The Director-General of the National Youth Service Corps, Brigadier General Shuaibu Ibrahim has advocated for more engagement with Nigerians on the invaluable contributions of the Scheme to the progress and development of the country. DG NYSC He recalled that it was a Corps Member who taught him History in Secondary School that inspired him to study History and today, he is an Associate Professor of History. He added that majority of the lawmakers are Ex-Corps Members who had positive service year experiences. He expressed gratitude and optimism for their continued support of the Scheme.